[
    {
        "content": "<p>Should we have this?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>Str.displayUtf8 : List U8 -&gt; Str\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>...where if it encounters any invalid UTF-8 sequences, it replaces them with the <a href=\"https://www.fileformat.info/info/unicode/char/fffd/index.htm\">Unicode Replacement Character</a>?</p>",
        "id": 456910091,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1722964104
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it's needed for the <code>Path</code> API, but not sure if it would be helpful elsewhere too <span aria-label=\"thinking\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f914\" role=\"img\" title=\"thinking\">:thinking:</span></p>",
        "id": 456910164,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1722964129
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe <code>Str.sanitizeUtf8</code>?</p>",
        "id": 456912587,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1722964728
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>displayUtf8</code> feels like it's just joining the utf-8 together</p>",
        "id": 456913470,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1722964970
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not sure about the name, but I like the function :)</p>",
        "id": 456914920,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1722965404
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This would be great</p>",
        "id": 456926118,
        "sender_full_name": "Isaac Van Doren",
        "timestamp": 1722968699
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Rust sometimes calls this <code>fromUtf8Lossy</code> but I don't like that because it sounds like it's always going to lose something (like lossy JPEG compression) but that's not really what's happening here</p>",
        "id": 456930510,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1722970324
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It does lose something</p>",
        "id": 456976037,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1722987278
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It loses any character that isn't valid utf8</p>",
        "id": 456976053,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1722987291
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So if you go back to utf8 from that string, you will have lost information. And instead have the urf8 replacement character</p>",
        "id": 456976119,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1722987339
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I definitely think this API should be <code>fromUtf8Something</code> to make it discoverable.</p>",
        "id": 456976202,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1722987387
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You could make it <code>fromUtf8WithReplacement</code> if you want to be really explicit.</p>",
        "id": 456976354,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1722987515
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"343810\">Brendan Hansknecht</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/Str.2EdisplayUtf8/near/456976037\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It does lose something<br>\nIt loses any character that isn't valid utf8</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>yeah I just think of \"lossy\" meaning \"you can expect it to lose something\" whereas this is more \"in very rare edge cases it can lose something\"</p>",
        "id": 456977215,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1722988162
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>Str.fromBytesReplaceInvalidUtf8</code></p>",
        "id": 456977644,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1722988458
    }
